elements.title: Christian Street Historic District
elements.contents: ... that the proposed Christian Street Historic District (building pictured), originally settled by Irish immigrants, is also known as "Black Doctors' Row"?

elements.title: Trudi Thomson
elements.contents: ... that twenty-a-day cigarette smoker Trudi Thomson suffered from bulimia and rheumatoid arthritis before she became a successful runner?

elements.title: Dash for Cash
elements.contents: ... that Dash for Cash, an event in which teachers competed to grab one-dollar bills to pay for school supplies, was criticized for being dehumanizing?

elements.title: Juan José Florián
elements.contents: ... that paracyclist Juan José Florián fought for both sides in the Colombian conflict?

elements.title: Third Street Railroad Trestle
elements.contents: ... that the Third Street Railroad Trestle is the last remaining wooden trestle bridge in downtown Austin, Texas?

elements.title: Xie Fei
elements.contents: ... that Xie Fei, one of the thirty women participating in the Long March, was imprisoned during the Cultural Revolution?

elements.title: Sei pezzi per pianoforte
elements.contents: ... that the Sei pezzi per pianoforte were Ottorino Respighi's first published works?

elements.title: Steve Jastrzembski
elements.contents: ... that Pittsburgh Panthers end Steve Jastrzembski was nicknamed "Jazz" because his teammates could not correctly pronounce his surname?
